The paper proposes new filtering algorithms for the SEQUENCE constraint and its extensions based on network flows. This involves optimization techniques and algorithms for maintaining bounds consistency over large domains. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) which deals with optimization, constraint satisfaction, and search algorithms. The paper also involves data structures and algorithms for efficient flow-based propagation, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The use of linear programming and optimization techniques also suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). Finally, the paper deals with global constraints, which could place it in the category of cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
